Aer I. SCENE 4.

Geta appears in great perturbation‚ having heard of the sudden arrival of Demipho. Phaedria and the slave try to screw Antipho's courage to the sticking-point, but in vain. When the old man is seen approaching Antipho hurriedly decamps, leaving his cousin to bear the brunt of his father’s anger.
